This paper deals with the representation of dynamic graphs using succinct data structures, which is a topic closely related to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), as well as data mining (cs.DM), computational complexity (cs.CC), and information retrieval (cs.IR). The use of compact representations of bit vectors also suggests a connection to digital libraries (cs.DL) and information storage and retrieval (cs.IR).
